{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"velvet-peridotite-blackmamba","description":"## Why\nThe single verified review-miss defect class in this store's history (E1 re-verifies: dc58, db7b, 5886) is a plan asserting a capability of an existing module that the module lacks. G1G2/E4 already tell reviewers to verify existence claims; the misses show asserted-CAPABILITY claims need a dedicated probe with teeth.\n\n## What\nAn asserted-capability grounding probe in the pass-1 G6/E4 rubric family: for each plan claim of the form \"module/tool X already does/handles Y\", the finder must locate the implementing symbol/behavior (grounding citation) or emit a finding. Inherits the existing blocking posture of its criteria family (G1G2 0.70 / E4 0.75) - no new blocking criterion. Implement ONLY if the gate row passes: E2 absent-capability mutants >=80% detected AND <=10% blocking-FP on controls AND E3 <=2% PASS->BLOCK flips on cleanly-closed tickets AND all 3 historical MISS plans surface the decisive finding above the advisory cap. Incorporated directly into the packaged rubrics on pass; a failing row defers the story with results recorded.\n\n## Scope\n- src/rebar/llm/reviewers/ G6/E4-family rubric prompts (+ prompt-index regeneration).\n- docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/ (gate-row results writeup consuming E2+E3 artifacts).\n- Unit/eval fixtures for the three historical miss plans.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The gate-row evidence is committed BEFORE the rubric change lands: E2 detection >=80% on absent-capability mutants, blocking-FP <=10% on controls, E3 PASS->BLOCK <=2%, and dc58/db7b/5886 each surface the decisive finding above the advisory cap.\n- [ ] The rubric change lands through Gerrit directly in the packaged prompts (no config flag), inheriting existing family posture - the blocking-criteria set does not grow.\n- [ ] docs/plan-review-gate.md documents the probe and cites the gate-row writeup.\n- [ ] If any gate-row leg fails, the story closes deferred with the failing numbers recorded instead of landing the change.","id":"59b7-69b6-e763-4a83","parent_id":"6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"R1: asserted-capability grounding probe (G6/E4 rubric family, gated on E2+E3)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784143925811149001,"uuid":"168fb83b-3203-4721-868f-377ed32c8c22"}